BCAA

What is BCAA?

BCAA, or Branched-Chain Amino Acids, are a group of three essential amino acids: leucine, isoleucine, and valine12. They are called “branched-chain” due to their unique chemical structure13. These amino acids are essential because our bodies cannot produce them, so they must be obtained from our diet12.
